The paper focuses on developing learning-based methods for 3D scene modeling and understanding, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) domains. The use of deep neural networks for room layout estimation suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) aspect to the work. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for generating textual descriptions of the 3D structures, which could potentially fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) category.
